Citation.sTitle: Vapor-Liquid Equilibrium for Carbon Dioxide + Isopropyl, Isobutyl, and Isoamyl Acetates
Citation.sAbstract: Vapor-liquid equilibrium of three acetates (isopropyl, isobutyl, and isoamyl acetate) + carbon dioxide were measured using a circulating-type equilibrium cell at temperature ranging from (313.2 to 333.2) K and pressure up to 10 MPa. The measured experimental data were correlated by the Peng-Robinson with conventional mixing rule and nonrandom lattice fluid with hydrogen bonding equations of state with a single binary interaction parameter.
